      "content": "i see. but isn't that kind of circular logic? if we punish people more heavily because they come from \"underserved\" areas, aren't we just making their situation even harder and increasing the chance they'll reoffend? basically, wouldn't a more equitable approach be to treat the crime itself as the focus, rather than using their socioeconomic status to justify a longer sentence for one and not the other?",
